- 50ml water;
- 150ml vegetable oil;
- 2 colored marker pens cartridges of your choice;
- A container of 250ml;
- Aspirinas;
- 1 lamp or flashlight.

- Dissolve the ink cartridges in water; 
- Pour the mixture of water and ink in the container; 
- Pour the oil onto the mixture in the container; 
- Place the aspirin in the container; 
- Turn the lamp/flashlight behind the container to illuminate the effect; 
- Add new aspirins to the container where the effervescent effect of reducing.

- 2 potatoes; 
- 2 pieces of zinc; 
- 2 pieces of copper; 
- 3 pieces of wire; 
- 1 calculator.

- Shove each piece of zinc in one of the ends of each potato; 
- Thread each piece of copper at the other end of each potato; 
- Roll one of the ends of the wire pieces in zinc piece of potatoes and the other end on the piece of copper from other potatoes; 
- Roll a one end of the other wire piece on another piece of zinc and the other end to the negative pole of the calculator; 
- Roll one of the ends of the last piece of wire on another piece of copper and the other end to the positive pole of the calculator.

